<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="repair-n">repair <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /rɪ'peə(r)/    美 /rɪ'per/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>修理；修补：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A man should keep his friendship in constant repair. 
只有经常维系，方能保持友谊天长地久。</p><footer>——约翰逊</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="beyond-repair">beyond repair</h3>
<p>1.<strong>无法修复</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="under-repair">under repair</h3>
<p>1.<strong>在修理中：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The castle built in 1432 is under repair. 
这座建于1432年的城堡正在修缮中。</p><footer>人教⑤ – 3</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>My washing machine <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (repair) this week, so I have to wash my clothes by hand.  （2018 天津改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. is being repaired  </p></div>